They are family books, but you'll find some very original fantasy reading in them (No Tolkien stereotypes).<br>
People don't usually consider Astrid Lindgren to be a fantasy writer, but i think that's mostly because 'fantasy' is actually real folklore here (We did the troll, gnome, elf, giant thing here 1000 years ago hehe).<br>
